In a message dated 3/8/03 7:23:42 AM Central Standard Time, 
cardhead649@... writes:


&gt; &quot;Everything?&quot;  Empath laughs bitterly.  &quot;Where to begin ... when the 
&gt; original Megatron and many of the Seekers were thrown off Astrotrain 
&gt; during Starscream&#39;s mutiny, they were picked up by Unicron.  The 
&gt; planet destroyer gave Megatron a choice: become Unicron&#39;s slave or 
&gt; die.  The bastard threw away his sanity and the lives of many strong, 
&gt; loyal Decepticons to become Galvatron.  Unicron made him some new 
&gt; troops from the ashes of the old, and he took over leadership of the 
&gt; Decepticons, keeping most of his power even after Unicron was 
&gt; destroyed.  He kept us all in line by sheer terror.  After the 
&gt; reformat, he was exiled for his crimes.  Now reduced to a blacklisted 
&gt; Predacon criminal, Galvatron was forced to use mind-altering control 
&gt; chips to gain followers.  I was one of these.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; Empath pauses for a moment, then continues.  &quot;Meanwhile, another 
&gt; Predacon took the name of Megatron and sought to steal enough energon 
&gt; to conquer Cybertron for himself.  A group of Maximals captured him 
&gt; and his crew and brought them back.  Some careless guards allowed him 
&gt; to escape with a new crew and he came here.  Galvatron also found his 
&gt; way here, with me still enslaved to his blasted Galvapred chip.  
&gt; While here, I found an artifact which set me free.  Galvatron ended 
&gt; up fusing with Megatron, and the rest you know.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; 

&quot;I see,&quot; before she can say any more, she received a transmission from 
Hydras:

&gt; After that Hydras send an encoded message to Maxima.
&gt; 
&gt; &quot;Maxima,
&gt; If you&#39;re inside Maximal&#39;s base you have to wait a while before do 
&gt; your mission. If you&#39;re now out or around, move quickly far of it. A 
&gt; cloud is around the base but it&#39;s the Plague. Be careful. As soon as 
&gt; you&#39;re far of Maximal Base&#39;s area  go to this area (gives a 
&gt; coordinates) and call me when you arrive there. Good luck.
&gt; 
&gt; Hydras&quot;
&gt; 

This slightly stunned her of his concern. But she quickly pushed it aside as 
she got up in beast mode & twisted around to see something that was 
surrounding the nearby  base. 

&quot;Might I suggest that we leave this area.... immediately, Empath!&quot;  

Then she glanced off in the direction of where the Ark may be. &quot;I know a 
place where we can go.&quot; taking a couple steps. &quot;Coming?&quot;

&quot;Otherwise,... if you stay, it will possibly be your doom.&quot; she thought about 
it... she just rescued Empath, in which Hydras wanted her dead... but... 
perhaps it was too soon to finish her off... she would still be needed... she 
was a Decepticon. 

